    "causal_summary": "The 004 capability run discriminated only on the margins: 3 of 4 hard fixtures saturated (both MiniMax-M3 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro scored 1.0), so correctness could not rank and the framework fell back to a format-TIE. The only signal was `hard-roman-to-int`, where MiMo's mean (0.627) came from a single catastrophic 0.0 across n=3 — a reliability blip, not a certified capability margin. The benchmark cannot yet CI-certify which model is better.",
